    "narrative": "For today\u2019s slate, **Jazz Chisholm Jr.** headlines our lineup with a commanding 79.92 efficiency score. His matchup against Arrighetti is our most favorable, benefiting from a high-upside SP matchup (5.10 xERA) and, crucially, a slow pitcher delivery that significantly boosts his stolen base potential. Similarly, **James Wood** (73.18) and **Corbin Carroll** (71.54) are essential starts; **Wood** leverages a massive 19% SP skill boost from Hudson, while **Carroll** remains a core anchor despite a tougher matchup against Michael King, as his floor is secured by his batting order spot and reliable xwOBA. **Tyler Soderstrom** (65.85) also warrants attention as a strong start, with the model identifying a significant 13% combined boost from his batting order and favorable right-handed platoon context.\n\nWe are navigating several risks today, particularly with players like **Seiya Suzuki** (49.86) and **Trevor Story** (55.08) facing elite arms like Wrobleski and Bradish. While the wind-out conditions provide a slight tailwind for **Suzuki**, the 19% penalty for facing a sub-3.00 xERA arm keeps him firmly in the middle of our utility range. Our most difficult bench decision involved **Vinnie Pasquantino**, who finished just shy of our 40-point floor at 39.32. The optimizer bypassed him primarily due to a severe 15% platoon penalty against Reid Detmers and an added layer of volatility from a 45% rain risk, forcing us to prioritize the higher-efficiency profiles of our starting infielders. We continue to monitor the \"Lineup Pending\" statuses for **Luis Campusano**, **Alex Freeland**, and **Trevor Story** to ensure these projected order slots hold before the first pitch.",
